ANSIBLE:
Before ansible:
	1. All tools are agent-based tools. Setting up infra is difficult.
	2. Other tools use pull mechanism.
	3. Managing grps, users are difficult.
	4. Installing or dealing with packages is some difficult.
	5. Backup data.


Pull mechanism: agent will pull configuration from main server.
Nodes will check the server.
They will pull commands if any changes are there.
Works continuosly.

Push mechanism: nodes will not check continuously.
Server(central server) sends commands to nodes.



After Ansible:
	1. It's  agent-less configuration, automated tool.
	2. It uses SSH protocol. --> gives more security.
	3. It uses push mechanism.
	4. It turns your code into infra.
	5. Tell desired configuration , don't need to mention how to achieve it.


PLAYBOOKS:
When dealing with multiple tasks, we will write what to perform.
It's an yaml files.

Advantage:
Not wasting time by executing one by one commands.

Why SSH?
Bcz of security features.
Secure, available in linux servers.
Will allows ansible to work without installing any agent in target servers(host servers).
When command is executed, it provides encrypted communication.


What is Ansible:
An automated tool helps us to manage, configure multiple servers automatically using SSH protocol
It's an agent-less tool.
